Not a moment goes by when I don’t think of how much I love you both and how truly grateful I am to be your Mumma. This will be our first Christmas since you where both born where we don’t get to wake up in the morning together. To watch you both full of joy and excitement opening your presents, Christmas music on and us dancing around the kitchen whilst I’m cooking your favourite food for Christmas lunch. I don’t usually share my “personal” life online, as I’m actually a very private person. But I’d just thought I’d send some extra love to the Mummas and Dads and caregivers out there who might not be spending this Christmas with their family and loved ones.

Christmas time can be a lot of things, and for some it’s all love and happiness, others, not so much. Just remember to focus on the good, create your own happiness and spread the love wherever you go. I’m grateful for my little adopted family this year for making me feel loved and special and celebrating Christmas with them until I get to see my little ones again. Remember, if you can be anything right now, be kind. You never know what others are going through, so spread kindness wherever you may wander. Merry Christmas Eve everyone, may all your dreams come true 🎄

Thank you @sammiespencer_ @spenny243 @jenniferorourke85 @james.will.turner @valeriebogolin for being my fam this Christmas and always, beyond grateful for your love 🤍

#Christmaseve #Love #Kindness

A gentle warrior lives inside each one of us, with an untapped reserve of overflowing power given to each of us by the universe itself.

It’s the aching place where the masculine and feminine meet in harmony and respect for each other.

As fierce as a Lion and as tender and innocent as a new born. 

After all, what is courage without deep tenderness and compassion?

What is strength without a side of raw sensitivity?

To be a gentle warrior is to have:
The soft touch of a mother, the unbreakable spirit of a fighter.

Bravery in all its essence as it’s defined; having or showing mental or moral strength to face Danger, fear, or difficulty, coupled with the sheer determination of a Predator who hunts its Prey.

A heart so vulnerable it hurts yet shows unconditional love with the ferocity of a Storm.

To be a gentle warrior is:

To break open and cry for seven days straight,  enduring suffering and still have a full heart. 

To walk softly into the dark flames of transformation, looking change directly in the eye with a lightning-like gaze.

To know that healing has to hurt.

To honor even the ugliest inner demons and understand that if we sit with our demons and not be afraid of them, they have so much to teach us.

To listen deeply; patiently; vulnerably and feel into the very core of our very being to find out who we truly are.

To not be afraid to stand up for what’s right.
To fight like hell.
To be intelligent enough to choose your battles wisely.
To take no action, at all.

To have the strength to walk through life with dignity, grace, honour and respect for one’s self, even when the only one who is watching is God himself. 

To recognise that the character of a person and their true colours are shown by how one treats others they feel negatively towards.

To have composure during the Storms and to be mature enough to take responsibility for our actions.

To recognise that if you have made as mistake, or done something wrong, how to apologise sincerely mean it. To learn from that mistake and take the lessons to help us grow.

To be a gentle warrior is to be brave enough to stand for something real, and tender enough to bow down to life, delicately.

Took a selfie for the first time after getting back from a walk in nature and kicking the soccer ball at the park to honour myself and who I am and what makes me happy 💚⚽️ 

I’ve taken some time off social media to focus on myself and what makes my heart feel full whilst pushing through the pain 🙏🏼 Healing from some pretty severe injuries and doing the work to get through that the best I can.

Healing isn’t pretty, it’s messy, it’s painful, its ugly, it’s angry, it’s tears and it’s tough work. But running from it only prolongs the healing process. 

Allowing myself to feel through it all and releasing what no longer serves me. Thankful for the prayer and breathwork I’ve been learning, it truly helps.

I’ve taken some time off social media to focus on what’s important. Raising my kids and finding my balance with life. Sending love to all everyone who’s working on themselves for themselves right now and doing the inner work.

Trying to be grateful for it all, although that in itself is a challenge. I have found the best place to start on your healing journey (wether it be physical, emotional etc) is honesty. 

Being honest with yourself is a great start point. Forgiving yourself and others (we all make mistakes) and then letting go. Standing up for yourself and allowing yourself to say NO to anything that doesn’t resonate with your heart. Finding what it is that makes YOU happy, not what you think will please others. For me it’s being able to create, going for a walk, going to the park and kicking a soccer ball, yoga, and seeing others happy. Being present with my children and finding balance with honouring need too 🤍

Thankful for all those incredible souls around me right now getting me through this, my family, my friends, my GP and my amazing Physio Erin at @optimumhealthsolutions for being so wonderful, for their care, their patience, advise and kindness 🤍

#healingjourney

There is so many special forms of Love in this world, and it begins with the Sacred Divine love from our family, our ancestors. I hold so much love for all of my ancestors for giving me this life, for your love, your teachings, your light and darkness has helped pave the way and shape us, your children. I have learnt many forms of love from my ancestors, and appreciate all the bonds that connect us. I thank God that I have a special piece of all my ancestors inside of my being. I honour  both the light and dark. Thank you all for being a guiding light in my darkness, and thank you for never leaving my side and protecting me and our families since the beginning. I believe our very being is intended to love in all its forms, we are taught to hate, to judge, and indifference through our conditionings here on Earth. No one person is better than another, and we all have a beautiful purpose given by God to create a better world for the next generation. I honour my ancestors, my soul families, my friends and everyone that I have had the blessing to meet. The light within me honours the light within you, the dark within me honours the dark within you. Thank you for helping me to let go of fear and choose love. If I could tell my younger self one thing, I would be to treasure your beautiful family, not just your blood family but your adopted family, your friends, and those who show you love in all its forms, listen to your elders, there stories are magic and there is so much you can learn when you listen, give a hug from your heart whenever you say goodbye to those you love, thank your parents for doing the best they could with what they have, judge less, listen more, see others perspectives and honour your inner child. Pray daily and practise gratitude whilst allowing yourself to feel through your pain. Never go to sleep on an argument with those you love and spread kindness wherever you wander. Don’t strive to be perfect, just try to be the best YOU can be. Let go. Let go of all that doesn’t serve you, be honest with yourself, and love yourself to your core. 

I see you, I am you, I love you 🤍 Thank you 🙏🏼

“Guardian Angel” Mixed Medium on canvas. Graphite, Acrylic with Rose Gold & Silver leafing 🕊

This piece holds a special place and significance to me, it represents all of those who we love that are no longer with us in human form, and have returned to Spirit as Angels. 

I’ve always felt a close connection to the Angelic Realm, and have always appreciated their presence, guidance and protection with much gratitude. Their unconditional love, peace and unity has helped me though life, especially in darker times. It has always bought me such a beautiful sense of peace knowing we have so many amazing Soul guides watching over us as we journey through this life.

In special memory of those friends and family members who have gone too soon, may we see each other again one day when our own Souls return to source 🤍

Just a appreciate post to share some love and healing to all the girls out their who suffer with horrible cramps each month and looking for some relief 🤍 I just wanted to say a thank you to @kosi_au for helping ease the pain I get each month with their amazing invention “Kosi”. Ever since I can remember I have dealt with severe pain and discomfort each month, my entire body aches especially my belly and lower back, I feel nauseous, fatigued, moody, have severe bloating from inflammation and insomnia due to pain. I have tried just about everything just to get some relief from my period pain and get on with my day. However Mum life never stops and when it’s that time of the month all I want to do is curl up in bed an cry, but who has time for that really? 

Panadol & warm epsom salt baths provide some relief, but I’ve found the older I get the worse the pain has become and even though I’d love to sit in a warm bath all day, that just not practical. 

When it’s really bad, my body even starts spasms which shoot up my back and down my legs which is not only painful but embarrassing to say the least. Even my kids always try to help with the pain and always offer me back rubs or to walk on my back just to get some relief 😢

The doctors have thought it could be endometriosis or just severe irregular period cramps, but no matter what they think it is, they always say the same thing “just get some rest, have some medicine and let your body recover”, which is all well and good, but as a Mum who still has a household to run, you don’t always get that luxury.

I’m so grateful for @kosi_au and their ingenious invention of the Kosi 360 degree, hands-free heat pack that wraps around your torso for complete heating and relief. Kosi is filled with Red Millet Seeds and Flaxseeds (Flaxseeds are reported to have pain-relieving and anti-inflammatory properties to provide you with an extra soothing affect.) and you can wear it at home, in your office or even under your clothes.

#kosi #womensupportingwomen #periodpain #selfcare
